CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 11, 1969 Page 15 reads: " Glamorous Brenda Jeter, of the trio of black models in Symphony Society Gala, wore a stunning black velvet and feathers evening gown with the covered-up look. Created by Oscar de la Renta, who was there to present his collection, the gown, sashed with satin, had the bare-look yoke."--Harris Photo  Related article states model is member of the Pittsburgh Negro Models Association.
TitMainTitle: Brenda Jeter modeling long dark velvet dress with feathered collar and cuffs at Symphony Society Gala.
